ngs demonstrate that climate, which is often cited as a key barrier to alien species establishment, may afford some protection to continental Antarctica, but that this protection is not currently extended to the Southern Ocean islands. Furthermore, existing climatic barriers to alien species establishment will weaken as warming continues across the region. This not only illustrates the value of applying distribution modelling methods to this largely ice-covered region, but demonstrates how these methods can be used to inform targeted surveillance of introduction pathways and sites that have the highest risk of establishment of invasive alien species.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Duffy, Grant A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Coetzee, Bernard W. T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Latombe, Guillaume", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Akerman, Alexander H.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "McGeoch, Melodie A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Chown, Steven L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Thuiller, Wilfried", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Chapter 2", "Chapter 3", "Chapter 6", "biodiversity", "environment assessment", "IPBES", "Alien Invasive Species Assessment AIS", "invasive species"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/86d92b1a1b9ddf6922b033667ea179be", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/5ebd0623815f388f7d4a26dfa28c7dafac1a11f79095e618d8380ae1fd7b8bba", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/2352922/items/GBVXGCCL", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/2352922/items/GBVXGCCL", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/98a5a737f4ac5bd111cbbd8a1d207602!/b30829-33323", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/359bd494433933b868f85e88d3437f76", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifi